On October 12, 1492, Christopher Columbus and his crew landed in The Bahamas, marking the beginning of the Age of Exploration. This proclamation recognizes Columbus as an important explorer and celebrates the contributions of Italian Americans to the United States. It also emphasizes the close bond between the United States and Italy. The proclamation calls on Americans to draw inspiration from Columbus's spirit of adventure and to continue exploring and understanding the wonders of the nation and the world. It states that October 14, 2019, is proclaimed as Columbus Day and encourages the observation of this day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.